This paper deals with the interpretability of predictive systems using high-dimensional behavioral and textual data. It proposes counterfactual explanations as a means of generating insight into model predictions. The paper also benchmarks the effectiveness and efficiency of different algorithms for finding counterfactuals. Given these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as they are the most relevant to the study of predictive systems and interpretability. The paper also deals with natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of predictive systems, which could place it under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
